        </example>

         <p>Now we will look at an application with graphing technology and put the points of interest in context.</p>

        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>A reduced-gravity aircraft is a fixed-wing airplane that astronauts use for training. The airplane flies up and then down in a parabolic path to simulate the feeling of weightlessness. In one training flight, the pilot will fly about 40-60 parabolic maneuvers. (You can read more on <url href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reduced-gravity_aircraft">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reduced-gravity<underscore/>aircraft</url>.)</p>

                <p>For the first parabolic maneuver, the height of the plane, in feet, at time <m>t</m>, in seconds, is given by <m>H(t)=-16t^2+400t+30500</m>.
                    <ol label="a.">
                        <li><p>Determine the starting altitude of the plane for the first maneuver.</p></li>

                        <li><p>What is the height of the plane <m>10</m> seconds into the maneuver?</p></li>

                        <li><p>Determine the maximum height of the plane and how long it takes to reach that height.</p></li>

                        <li><p>The zero-gravity effect is experienced when the plane begins the parabolic path until it gets back down to <m>30{,}500</m> feet. Write an inequality to express this and solve it using the graph. Write the times of the zero-gravity effect as an interval and determine how long the astronauts experience weightlessness during each cycle.</p></li>

                        <li><p>Use technology to make a table of <m>H(t)</m> with <m>t</m>-values from <m>0</m> to <m>25</m> seconds. Use an increment of <m>5</m> seconds and then use the table to solve <m>H(t)=32100</m>.</p></li>

                        <li><p>State the domain and range for this context.</p></li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>We can answer the questions based on the information in the graph.</p>
                    <figure>
                        <caption>Graph of <m>H(t)=-16t^2+400t+305000</m> with <m>y=30500</m></caption>
                            <image width="80%">
                                <description></description>
                                <latex-image>
                                    <![CDATA[\begin{tikzpicture}
                                      \begin{axis}[
                                        axis line style={->},
                                        ymin=-50,
                                        ymax=450,
                                        xmin=-5,
                                        xmax=30,
                                        xtick = {0,10,...,30},
                                        minor xtick = {-5, 0, ..., 30},
                                        ytick = {0,100,...,400},
                                        yticklabels = {0,10000,20000,30000,40000},
                                        minor ytick = {-50,0,...,450},
                                        xlabel={time in seconds},ylabel={height in feet},
                                        clip=false]
                                    \addplot+[domain=-5:30] {(-16*x^2+400*x+30500)/100} node[right] {$y=H(t)$};
                                      \addplot+[domain=-5:30] {30500/100} node[above right] {$y=30500$};
                                    \addplot [soliddot] coordinates {(0,305)} node[below right] {$(0,30500)$};
                                    \addplot [soliddot] coordinates {(25,305)} node[below left] {$(25,30500)$};
                                    \addplot [soliddot] coordinates {(10,329)} node[above left] {$(10,32900)$};
                                    \addplot [soliddot] coordinates {(12.5,330)} node[above right] {$(32.5,34000)$};
                                \end{axis}
                            \end{tikzpicture}  

                            ]]>
                                </latex-image>
                            </image>
                        </figure>

                               
                <p><ol label="a.">
                        <li><p>The starting height is the vertical intercept, which is <m>(0,30500)</m>. The feeling of weightlessness begins at <m>30{ , }500</m> feet.</p></li>

                        <li><p>After <m>10</m> seconds, the height of the plane is <m>32{,}900</m> feet.</p></li>

                        <li><p>For the maximum height of the plane we look at the vertex, which is approximately <m>(12.5, 33000)</m>. This tells us that after <m>12.5</m> seconds the plane will be at its maximum height of <m>33,000</m> feet.</p></li>

                        <li><p>We can write an inequality to describe when the plane is at or above <m>30{,}500</m> feet and solve it graphically. 
                        
                        <me>-16t^2+400t+30500\ge30500</me>. 

                        We graph the line <m>y=30500</m> and find the points of intersection with the parabola. The astronauts experience weightlessness from <m>0</m> seconds to <m>25</m> seconds into the maneuver, or <m>[0,25]</m> seconds. They experience weightlessness for 25 seconds in each cycle.</p></li>

                        <li><p>To solve <m>H(t)=32100</m> using the table, we look for where the <m>H</m>-values are equal to <m>32100</m>. There are two solutions, <m>5</m> seconds and <m>20</m> seconds. The solution set is <m>\{5,20\}</m>.</p>
