            <!-- Solving Graphically -->
            <exercise>
              <webwork >
                <pg-macros>
                    <macro-file>PCCgraphMacros.pl</macro-file>
                </pg-macros>
                <setup>
                    <var name="$func">
                      <static>3t^2+5t</static>
                    </var>
                    <var name="$acceleration">
                      <static>3</static>
                    </var>
                    <var name="$v0">
                      <static>5</static>
                    </var>
                    <var name="$t1">
                      <static>10</static>
                    </var>
                    <var name="$d1">
                      <static>350</static>
                    </var>
                    <var name="$alt">
                      <static>\text{This picture shows the graph of a parabola for the function }d(t)=3t^2+5t\text{. A horizontal line, }y=350\text{, is graphed, and the intersections of }d(t)\text{ and }y=350, (10,350),\text{ are labeled.}</static>
                    </var>
                    <pg-code>
                        $refreshCachedImages=1;
                        Context("Numeric");
                        Context()->variables->add(t => 'Real');
                        Context()->flags->set(showExtraParens=>0, reduceConstants=>0);
                        Context()->noreduce("(-x)-y","(-x)+y");
                        Context()->flags->set(
                          tolerance => 0.005,
                          tolType => "absolute",
                        );

                        $acceleration = random(1,5,0.1);
                        $v0 = random(3,10,1);
                        $a = $acceleration/2;
                        $b = $v0;

                        $func = Compute("$a*t**2+$b*t")->reduce;
                        $funcX = Compute("$a*x**2+$b*x")->reduce;

                        $t1 = random(5,20,1);
                        $d1 = $func->eval(t=>$t1);

                        $alt="This picture shows the graph of a parabola for the function d(t)=$func. A horizontal line y=$d1 is graphed, and the intersections of d(t) and y=$d1, ($t1,$d1), are labeled.";

                        ($min[0], $max[0], $min[1], $max[1], $ticknum[0], $ticknum[1], $xticks_ref, $yticks_ref, $marksep[0], $marksep[1]) = NiceGraphParameters([0,$t1],[$d1,0]);

                        @xticks = @$xticks_ref;
                        @yticks = @$yticks_ref;

                        $gr = init_graph($min[0],$min[1],$max[0],$max[1],
                           axes=>[0,0],
                           grid=>[$ticknum[0],$ticknum[1]],
                           size=>[xPixels(),yPixels()]
                        );
                        $gr->lb('reset');
                        for my $j (@xticks) {
                            if (abs($j) &lt; 10**(-10)) {next;}
                            $gr->lb( new Label($j, -$marksep[1]/8, $j,'black','center','top'));
                        }
                        $gr->lb( new Label($max[0]-$marksep[0]/2, $marksep[1]/8, t,'black','center','bottom'));
                        $gr->lb( new Label($marksep[0]/8, $max[1]-$marksep[1]/2, d,'black','left','middle'));

                        for my $j (@yticks) {
                            if (Real($j) == 0) {next;}
                            $gr->lb( new Label(-$marksep[0]/8, $j, $j,'black','right','middle'));
                        }

                        add_functions($gr, "$funcX for x in &lt; 0,$max[0]> using color:red and weight:1");
                        add_functions($gr, "$d1 for x in &lt; $min[0],$max[0]> using color:blue and weight:1");
                        $gr->lb( new Label($t1/2, $d1-$marksep[1]/8, "y=$d1",'blue','center','top'));

                        $hx = $t1/2;
                        $hy = $func->eval(t=>$hx);
                        $gr->lb( new Label($hx-$marksep[0]/8, $hy, "d(t)",'red','right','middle'));

                        $gr->stamps( closed_circle($t1,$d1,'red') );
                        $gr->lb( new Label($t1-$marksep[0]/8, $d1+$marksep[1]/8, "($t1,$d1)",'red','right','bottom'));
                    </pg-code>
                </setup>
                <statement>
                    <p>In a race, a car drove through the starting line at the speed of <m><var name="$v0"/></m> meters per second. It was accelerating at <m><var name="$acceleration"/></m> meters per second squared. Its distance from the starting position can be modeled by the function <m>d(t)=<var name="$func"/></m>. Find the answer using technology.</p>

                    <p>After <var name="$t1" width="10" /> seconds, the car was <m><var name="$d1"/></m> meters away from the starting position.</p>
                </statement>
                <solution>
                    <p>Use technology to graph the functions <m>d(t)=<var name="$func"/></m> and <m>y=<var name="$d1"/></m>, and find the point of intersection where <m>x</m> is positive, <m>(<var name="$t1"/>,<var name="$d1"/>)</m>.</p>
                    <figure>
                      <image pg-name="$gr">
                          <description><var name="$alt" /></description>
                      </image>
                    </figure>
                    <p>According to the point of intersection, the car was <m><var name="$d1"/></m> meters away from the starting position after <m><var name="$t1"/></m> seconds.</p>
